description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;There is currently a vacancy for a highly motivated Band 5 Registered Nurse within the Endoscopy unit at Kent &amp; Canterbury Hospital. The unit is a busy Unit delivering high quality care to patients attending for both diagnostic and therapeutic procedures. This post is permanent.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;For this Band 5 position we require you to have enthusiasm and drive, 6 months experience as a Band 5 in an acute Hospital setting and preferably have Endoscopy experience although nurses with transferable skills would be considered and full training will be given which is competency based training. The candidate must be willing to continue with professional development and be aware of the Trusts’ mission and values.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;East Kent Hospitals University Foundation Trust is one of the largest Trusts in England and is situated in the heart of the “Garden of England.” The Trust has three endoscopy Units located on all three main sites at the Queen Elizabeth the Queen Mother Hospital in Margate at the William Harvey Hospital in Ashford and the third located at the Kent &amp; Canterbury Hospital. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;So should you require more details or wish to arrange an informal visit then please contact&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Julie Phillips Endoscopy unit Manager on 01227-766877 extension 722-5047&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Or via e mail--- jphillips11@nhs.net&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
